beer.beer_description: In collaboration with Three Mills Bakery we brewed a Kvass; a truly ancient style of beer made for generations. Using bread that would otherwise be thrown out we took 20 kilos of stale rye, added it to the mash and used a sourdough starter in the wort to create a doughy, sour brew. This beer is truly liquid bread!
